  "prompt": "Were any real sets built for The Lego movie?",
  "response": "Yes, **The LEGO Group** released a wide variety of real LEGO sets specifically designed for *The LEGO Movie*. These sets allowed fans to build and interact with iconic characters, vehicles, and locations featured in the film. Here's an overview of some notable aspects:\n\n### **Character Sets**\n- **Emmet's Dream House/Rescue Headquarters**: This set includes Emmet, along with his friends like Batman, Unikitty, and others, enabling fans to recreate their adventures.\n- **Wyldstyle's Crashin\u2019 Drone Truck**: Featuring the fearless Wyldstyle, this set includes her customized drone truck equipped for action-packed missions.\n- **Batman\u2019s Mech Vehicle**: A detailed set showcasing Batman in his robotic mech suit, complete with weapons and movable parts.\n\n### **Vehicle Sets**\n- **Suburban Legends**: A large, multi-level police cruiser inspired by the blue police cars seen in the movie, complete with Minifigures like President Business and an undercover cop.\n- **Lord Business' Vehicle**: This set includes Lord Business in his high-tech vehicle, emphasizing his role as the antagonist in the film.\n\n### **Location Sets**\n- **Bricksburg City**: Featuring key landmarks from the movie, this set allows builders to recreate the vibrant cityscape where much of the movie's action takes place.\n- **Cloud Cuckoo Palace**: A whimsical, floating kingdom that serves as the home of Unikitty and her whimsical subjects.\n\n### **Special Editions and Promos**\n- **Bonus Packs and Exclusive Sets**: LEGO also released exclusive promotional sets during the movie's marketing campaign, often available through special events or retailers.\n\n### **Collaborations and Expansions**\n- **The LEGO Movie 2 Sets**: Following the success of the first movie, LEGO continued to expand the universe with additional sets based on *The LEGO Movie 2: The Second Part*.\n\nThese sets not only served as merchandise but also enhanced the fan experience by allowing enthusiasts to engage creatively with the movie's universe. They were available through various retail channels, LEGO stores, and online platforms, often limited in quantity to maintain exclusivity and demand.\n\n**Additional Resources:**\n- [Official LEGO The LEGO Movie Sets](https://www.lego.com/en-us/themes/the-lego-movie/about)\n- [BrickLink's Comprehensive LEGO Movie Collection](https://www.bricklink.com/v2/catalog.page?q=the+lego+movie&categoryID=all)\n\nIf you're interested in collecting these sets or learning more about them, visiting the official LEGO website or specialized LEGO retailers can provide detailed information and availability.",
